args: Um, could I talk to all of you for a second?
I think I know what the problem was\nwith the tea parties.
Well, you tried to make your first party\nreally fancy because he's a king, right?
One should do no less for royalty.
Okay, but I don't think that's the kind\nof party he actually wanted.
He didn't want some fancy party—he just\nwanted to have fun with everyone!
But he felt lonely and distanced when\neveryone was being all fussy because\nhe's the king.
As the Hare said, there's a certain standard\none must uphold when it comes to a king.
Right, and I get that—but what you need\nto do is put your hearts into it!

Yeah! If you put your heart into setting up
the party, I'm sure he'll be able to tell
how much you want to enjoy it with him!
So, um...what do you think?
I think I see what you're saying, but...
You are making a joke, yes? A fine jape?\nPut our hearts into a party for THAT tyrant?
I refuse. I don't like it.
I also refuse. If it were a girl, I'd be happy\nto pour my heart into it, but for that guy...
I really can't do anything right...
Elias was wrong—there isn't a darn thing\nI can do that someone else can't do better.
The tea party with my younger brother\nseemed to be such a fun time, yet when\nI attempted to do the same thing...
But if I give up, he'll be lonely like that\nfor the rest of his life...
Enough, Pia! No more tears! I'm gonna do\nsomething even if I have to do it alone!
All right, I need thiiis much scone dough...
Got it. Next, I'll boil the water for\nwarming the pot and cups...
I wonder if the elder-brother king likes\ngrape jam? I could make some for him...
Now for the rest of the treats... Oh!
Oh, poo! I spilled the fresh cream!\nI need a washcloth...
All right, it's all pretty now. I just have to\nwarm the cup with water and... Eeek!
And I cut my poor finger... *sniff*\nWell, better get it cleaned up.
No time for crying here—I've got to throw\na tea party the elder brother will love!
Show me your cut. I'll make it better.
The Hatter? But how did you...?
I can't help you with my tiny body,\nso I went to people who could.
Pia, if we may, why do you work so hard\nfor the elder king?
I guess 'cause I understand his feelings.
But you and he are nothing alike.\nHow can this be?
Actually, because I'm a child, I know\nexactly how it feels to be treated\ndifferently, and I don't like it.
See, I've actually come here from a\ndifferent world.
And in that world, I've been trying to help\nall the people who are important to me.
But there were a lot of things they wouldn't\nlet me do because I'm still just a kid.
I know they're doing it for my own sake,\nbut I still don't like it.
And that's why I don't want to let the\nelder king keep feeling that way.
I well understand how kind you are now,\nand yet we also don't want you to get hurt.
What if you put all this hard work in and\nhe simply yells at you all over again?
That's fine. Even if he gets all scream-y,\nhe'll know I put my heart into it.
I learned that with my choir. A song that\nyou put your whole heart into conveys\nyour feelings to the people who hear it.
I've got a long way to go before\nI'm a grown-up. I know that.
But even a kid can put their heart into\nsomething, and that's what I'm gonna do!
The fire was getting dangerous, so I put it\nout. Your water was about to boil over.
Yikes! I got so caught up in what I was\nsaying, I forgot about it. Thank you!
With pleasure. And I must say, I do like\nthe ring of this ＂tea party one puts their\nheart into＂ idea you're espousing.
I'm rather looking forward to it.\nMight you allow me to help?
Just a moment there, Cheshire Spider.\nIt's terribly unfair of you to show up\nand attempt to steal the show.
Why, I myself was JUST thinking how\nthis looked like a rollicking good time!
I would like to participate in the\ntea party planning as well.
I don't think we've HAD a tea party where\nwe really put our hearts into it.
We should all pitch in as we can.
Let's all work together to make this\nthe funnest tea party ever!
